WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.965 --> 00:00:09.926
[bright. energetic music playing]

2
00:00:16.975 --> 00:00:18.184
[Kitty] <i>You've got this. Kitty.</i>

3
00:00:18.268 --> 00:00:20.770
<i>You've pulled an all-nighter</i>
<i>every day this week.</i>

4
00:00:20.854 --> 00:00:23.106
<i>It's just a test. Kitty.</i>

5
00:00:23.189 --> 00:00:26.526
<i>Except. if Jiwon fails you.</i>
<i>you can kiss NYU goodbye.</i>

6
00:00:26.609 --> 00:00:28.278
<i>and you'll scrub toilets in Portland</i>

7
00:00:28.361 --> 00:00:30.697
<i>for the rest</i>
<i>of your godforsaken life. and…</i>

8
00:00:30.780 --> 00:00:32.323
<i>No. no. stop.</i>

9
00:00:35.952 --> 00:00:37.454
Pencils down. everyone.

10
00:00:37.537 --> 00:00:40.790
Seniors. don't forget to go to the lounge
for an announcement.

11
00:00:41.541 --> 00:00:44.044
Thank you. Thank you.

12
00:00:45.211 --> 00:00:47.797
- Feeling good?
- Better than good. Great.

13
00:00:47.881 --> 00:00:51.301
I spent the last week
becoming one with the text.

14
00:00:51.384 --> 00:00:54.763
- So. when are we gonna get our grades?
- You'll get the verdict sometime tomorrow.

15
00:00:56.056 --> 00:00:58.475
Yay! So soon.

16
00:00:59.476 --> 00:01:00.477
<i>No pressure.</i>

17
00:01:00.560 --> 00:01:03.438
<i>Not like my future</i>
<i>is hanging in the balance.</i>

18
00:01:06.107 --> 00:01:10.236
Can you check my pulse?
Professor Lee's exam killed me.

19
00:01:10.320 --> 00:01:13.364
I barely had time to study
since I started working for Yisoo.

20
00:01:13.448 --> 00:01:15.408
But I'm getting paid today.
so there's that.

21
00:01:15.492 --> 00:01:18.119
Ooh. So I'm hearing lunch is on you?
I'm craving <i>bibimbap.</i>

22
00:01:18.203 --> 00:01:20.789
Oh. ha ha. Actually.
I do have something for you.

23
00:01:22.123 --> 00:01:24.250
My mom found it while she was unpacking.

24
00:01:25.001 --> 00:01:28.421
Is this our moms on a rollercoaster?

25
00:01:28.505 --> 00:01:31.549
Yes. it's the French Revolution ride
at Lotte World.

26
00:01:33.259 --> 00:01:35.220
Can you believe my mom ever had fun?

27
00:01:35.303 --> 00:01:38.056
I like to think
they brought out the best in each other.

28
00:01:39.390 --> 00:01:40.475
Wait. stop. is that--

29
00:01:40.558 --> 00:01:42.644
[Yuri] Yeah.
that's Professor Lee with a perm.

30
00:01:42.727 --> 00:01:45.105
[chuckles] This is so much better
than a free lunch.

31
00:01:45.188 --> 00:01:48.233
Wait. we should totally recreate
this photo before the year's up.

32
00:01:48.316 --> 00:01:49.984
Yes. I'm adding that to my list.

33
00:01:50.777 --> 00:01:52.445
- Hey. Hi.
- Oh. hi.

34
00:01:52.529 --> 00:01:54.155
[clears throat]

35
00:01:55.573 --> 00:01:57.492
Congratulations on finishing
your midterms.

36
00:01:57.575 --> 00:01:59.369
You've all worked hard.

37
00:01:59.452 --> 00:02:01.579
Some. harder than others.

38
00:02:02.580 --> 00:02:05.500
And while I believe
education is its own reward.

39
00:02:05.583 --> 00:02:07.335
I'm not above a little fun.

40
00:02:07.418 --> 00:02:10.380
Which is why
this year's senior field trip is to…

41
00:02:15.093 --> 00:02:16.261
Hm.

42
00:02:17.554 --> 00:02:19.180
The Korean Furniture Museum!

43
00:02:19.264 --> 00:02:21.432
- [gasps]
- [students groan]

44
00:02:24.018 --> 00:02:26.396
Last year they went to the Stamp Museum.

45
00:02:26.479 --> 00:02:28.356
This might be worse.

46
00:02:31.401 --> 00:02:32.485
Uh. Professor Lee?

47
00:02:33.611 --> 00:02:36.990
As riveting
as the Furniture Museum sounds…

48
00:02:37.073 --> 00:02:39.325
I mean. who doesn't love a good ottoman?

49
00:02:39.409 --> 00:02:42.495
But what if we went
to Lotte World instead?

50
00:02:43.454 --> 00:02:45.915
This isn't a Socratic forum. Ms. Covey.

51
00:02:45.999 --> 00:02:48.501
The senior field trip
is supposed to be educational.

52
00:02:48.585 --> 00:02:51.629
Uh. there's lots of walking
at Lotte World.

53
00:02:51.713 --> 00:02:53.756
which is physical education.

54
00:02:53.840 --> 00:02:55.133
[quietly] Please help me.

55
00:02:55.216 --> 00:02:57.427
Lotte is one of the biggest brands
in Korea.

56
00:02:57.510 --> 00:03:00.430
I mean. is there a better way
to study business marketing?

57
00:03:00.513 --> 00:03:04.934
And. um. roller coasters
are basically applied physics.

58
00:03:05.018 --> 00:03:07.979
- I've literally always said that. So…
- Thank you.

59
00:03:08.062 --> 00:03:10.690
[Kitty] And you didn't object
to Lotte World

60
00:03:10.773 --> 00:03:11.900
when you were in high school.

61
00:03:16.654 --> 00:03:18.656
[gentle music playing]

62
00:03:19.616 --> 00:03:21.117
[Kitty] Nice perm. by the way.

63
00:03:21.201 --> 00:03:23.161
Never imagined you with ringlets.

64
00:03:26.372 --> 00:03:28.041
Where'd you find this?

65
00:03:28.124 --> 00:03:29.459
Yuri got it from her mom.

66
00:03:30.418 --> 00:03:32.170
It looks like an amazing memory.

67
00:03:35.173 --> 00:03:36.174
It was.

68
00:03:42.847 --> 00:03:43.848
Lotte World it is.

69
00:03:43.932 --> 00:03:46.309
[students cheer]

70
00:03:47.352 --> 00:03:48.853
- [gasps]
- [clears throat]

71
00:03:49.979 --> 00:03:51.898
We're going to Lotte World!

72
00:03:51.981 --> 00:03:53.983
[bright. energetic music playing]

73
00:03:59.197 --> 00:04:02.158
Call me crazy. but I think
the arcade's the best part of the park.

74
00:04:02.242 --> 00:04:04.744
Okay. Then you're crazy.
Have you even been on the Conquistador?

75
00:04:04.827 --> 00:04:06.996
There he is. Man of the hour.

76
00:04:07.080 --> 00:04:09.290
Congratulations on breaking
the school record.

77
00:04:09.374 --> 00:04:13.044
It's the fastest 100-meter hurdles
that KISS has ever seen.

78
00:04:14.170 --> 00:04:15.922
Thanks. Just had a good morning.

79
00:04:16.005 --> 00:04:17.715
Jin. wasn't that your record though?

80
00:04:17.799 --> 00:04:20.969
- Records were made to be broken.
- Yeah. but by 0.3 seconds though.

81
00:04:21.052 --> 00:04:22.845
[inhales sharply] Yikes.

82
00:04:26.975 --> 00:04:29.727
- Are you sure you're okay with all this?
- Of course.

83
00:04:29.811 --> 00:04:31.896
Told you. I'm happy for you.

84
00:04:37.944 --> 00:04:41.489
Did you guys finish your applications?
I got mine into SNU a week ago.

85
00:04:41.572 --> 00:04:42.448
Already?

86
00:04:42.532 --> 00:04:44.701
Early apps aren't due
for another few weeks.

87
00:04:44.784 --> 00:04:47.245
Yeah. but. you know. it's my dream school.

88
00:04:47.328 --> 00:04:50.790
and Korean unis are getting
harder to get into each year.

89
00:04:50.873 --> 00:04:52.542
I have no doubt you're gonna get in.

90
00:04:52.625 --> 00:04:55.169
Wait. are you kidding me? [scoffs]

91
00:04:55.253 --> 00:04:56.337
Are you okay?

92
00:04:56.921 --> 00:04:59.632
Uh. I just got my first direct deposit.

93
00:05:00.216 --> 00:05:02.218
Where is the rest of it?

94
00:05:02.302 --> 00:05:04.137
Girl. everyone has to start somewhere.

95
00:05:04.220 --> 00:05:06.389
[Eunice squeals]

96
00:05:06.472 --> 00:05:10.310
Did you see? My music video
just hit 10 on the K-pop 100!

97
00:05:10.393 --> 00:05:13.396
What?! Seriously?
Yesterday it was. like. ranked 78!

98
00:05:13.479 --> 00:05:16.816
I know. right? And Jennie.
she just followed me on Instagram!

99
00:05:16.899 --> 00:05:19.986
- No way. What? No way.
- Oh my gosh. shut up. Shut up.

100
00:05:20.069 --> 00:05:23.448
- No!
- All right. Eunice! I knew you'd smash it!

101
00:05:23.531 --> 00:05:25.867
Hey. you are smashing it also.

102
00:05:25.950 --> 00:05:28.786
Congrats to you for making it happen.
I'm so proud of you.

103
00:05:28.870 --> 00:05:30.288
- Thanks. Kitty.
- [cell phone chimes]

104
00:05:36.252 --> 00:05:38.379
{\an8}Oh wow. Um. my dad just said

105
00:05:38.463 --> 00:05:42.216
he wants to start recording Eunice's album
straight after graduation.

106
00:05:42.300 --> 00:05:46.220
Oh. that's awesome. I can't believe
you know what you're doing next year.

107
00:05:46.304 --> 00:05:49.349
Yeah. I guess it means
I'm staying in Seoul.

108
00:05:49.432 --> 00:05:51.100
[Kitty sighs]

109
00:05:51.184 --> 00:05:52.352
What about you?

110
00:05:52.435 --> 00:05:57.315
I know you love NYU.
but have you ever thought about staying?

111
00:05:57.398 --> 00:06:00.860
[Kitty] <i>Whoa. future talk?</i>
<i>This is new territory.</i>

112
00:06:00.943 --> 00:06:05.365
<i>Of course I've thought about staying</i>
<i>in Seoul for college. just a little.</i>

113
00:06:05.448 --> 00:06:06.866
I don't know. Maybe.

114
00:06:07.950 --> 00:06:11.204
I mean. I could get
an apartment in Itaewon.

115
00:06:11.287 --> 00:06:13.539
See Jiwon and Imo-Halmoni all the time.

116
00:06:13.623 --> 00:06:15.458
- Maybe see Yuri get a raise.
- [chuckles]

117
00:06:15.541 --> 00:06:19.712
And you and I still have
a lot to cross off my sunset list.

118
00:06:19.796 --> 00:06:23.174
And I might just have
a few things to add to it.

119
00:06:23.925 --> 00:06:26.552
[chuckles softly] It could be
kind of amazing.

120
00:06:26.636 --> 00:06:29.472
But for now.
let's make today unforgettable.

121
00:06:29.555 --> 00:06:31.682
["100!" by One Pact playing]

122
00:06:31.766 --> 00:06:32.892
<i>♪ OP ♪</i>

123
00:06:33.726 --> 00:06:37.772
<i>♪ 'Cause I don't mind</i>
<i>Lookin' for somebody like you… ♪</i>

124
00:06:37.855 --> 00:06:41.317
[pop song continues in Korean]

125
00:06:48.324 --> 00:06:50.326
Now. remember
to use the buddy system. guys.

126
00:06:50.410 --> 00:06:53.454
- It's okay. They're not toddlers.
- Worse. they're teenagers.

127
00:06:53.538 --> 00:06:55.039
- [exclaims]
- I'm so in!

128
00:06:55.123 --> 00:06:56.499
[Alex] Oh shoot. they're running.

129
00:06:56.582 --> 00:06:58.543
- Whoa. whoa. whoa. Slow down.
- Whoa!

130
00:06:58.626 --> 00:06:59.627
[excited chatter]

131
00:06:59.710 --> 00:07:03.506
[in Korean] Hello. hello.
Please show your tickets.

132
00:07:03.589 --> 00:07:04.715
[gasps]

133
00:07:05.675 --> 00:07:08.136
- Eunice?! From the music video?
- That's me!

134
00:07:08.719 --> 00:07:11.597
[in English] ♪ <i>All the boys wanna see me</i>
<i>All the girls wanna be me </i>♪

135
00:07:11.681 --> 00:07:14.100
<i>♪ At the end of the night</i>
<i>All the girls and the guys </i>♪

136
00:07:14.183 --> 00:07:16.394
[both squeal and laugh]

137
00:07:16.477 --> 00:07:18.229
[in Korean] I'm your number one "Eunit."

138
00:07:18.312 --> 00:07:19.522
Really? Thank you!

139
00:07:19.605 --> 00:07:22.733
I can get you and your friends
through the VIP entrance.

140
00:07:22.817 --> 00:07:24.068
Really?

141
00:07:24.152 --> 00:07:26.571
[in English] They're gonna let us
in the VIP line!

142
00:07:26.654 --> 00:07:29.866
[in Korean] Thank you! Find me later
and let's take a picture together!

143
00:07:29.949 --> 00:07:31.159
Thank you!

144
00:07:31.242 --> 00:07:32.785
[giggles]

145
00:07:33.286 --> 00:07:35.496
- [Eunice in English] I'm so excited!
- Sorry.

146
00:07:35.997 --> 00:07:37.165
Oh my God!

147
00:07:40.251 --> 00:07:42.503
Wait. you two smile and say VIP!

148
00:07:42.587 --> 00:07:44.464
- Oh. That is such a nice idea!
- Sure.

149
00:07:45.256 --> 00:07:47.842
- VIP!
- Yay!

150
00:07:49.218 --> 00:07:51.971
Nice! Yeah. great!

151
00:07:52.847 --> 00:07:53.973
[speaks Korean]

152
00:07:54.932 --> 00:07:56.601
Where did everybody go?

153
00:07:56.684 --> 00:07:59.270
Oh shoot. I just zoned out.

154
00:08:00.188 --> 00:08:03.274
But you know what?
You deserve to have a little bit of fun.

155
00:08:03.357 --> 00:08:05.276
Maybe catch a ride or two.

156
00:08:05.359 --> 00:08:08.654
We should totally get the school uniforms.

157
00:08:08.738 --> 00:08:12.033
It'd be super nostalgic.
It's a Lotte World tradition.

158
00:08:12.116 --> 00:08:14.202
Professor Finnerty. we're the adults.

159
00:08:14.285 --> 00:08:17.038
- We're here to keep the students safe.
- [sighs]

160
00:08:17.121 --> 00:08:18.956
Come on. just one ride?

161
00:08:19.916 --> 00:08:21.167
Mm.

162
00:08:23.461 --> 00:08:25.463
[riders scream]

163
00:08:27.840 --> 00:08:29.884
Are you sure
this is the same roller coaster?

164
00:08:29.967 --> 00:08:34.138
- It looks. like. way bigger in person.
- Hey. if our moms did it. so can we.

165
00:08:37.558 --> 00:08:41.354
Do you know what happens inside
that tunnel? Actually. I don't wanna know.

166
00:08:41.437 --> 00:08:44.398
Kitty Song-Covey.
afraid of a roller coaster?

167
00:08:44.899 --> 00:08:47.735
- You feeling all right?
- Totally.

168
00:08:47.818 --> 00:08:50.112
Just occurred to me
that this is older than we are.

169
00:08:50.196 --> 00:08:52.031
so it might be. like. a safety hazard.

170
00:08:52.114 --> 00:08:53.491
Trust your instincts. Kathy.

171
00:08:53.574 --> 00:08:55.910
There's over 100
theme park-related deaths per year.

172
00:08:55.993 --> 00:08:59.121
Why do you think they call it
the French Revolution?

173
00:08:59.205 --> 00:09:01.499
Your head's too big as it is.
No one will miss it.

174
00:09:01.582 --> 00:09:04.377
All right. you two.
you don't have to be friends.

175
00:09:05.211 --> 00:09:06.671
I'll settle for frenemies.

176
00:09:06.754 --> 00:09:08.381
- Never gonna happen.
- Keep dreaming.

177
00:09:11.676 --> 00:09:14.136
Maybe I just. you know.
work my way up to it.

178
00:09:15.137 --> 00:09:16.305
That's a great idea.

179
00:09:16.389 --> 00:09:19.350
We'll all meet at the entrance at 10 p.m..
and ride together.

180
00:09:19.433 --> 00:09:20.643
- Let's do it.
- Sounds good.

181
00:09:20.726 --> 00:09:22.270
- 'Kay.
- We'll get you your photo.

182
00:09:22.353 --> 00:09:24.146
It'll be the last thing we do.

183
00:09:25.147 --> 00:09:27.817
In the park. Covey. Not in life.

184
00:09:27.900 --> 00:09:30.695
That gives us a few hours.
Should we hit the Conquistador?

185
00:09:30.778 --> 00:09:33.114
Actually. you were right.
We should do the arcade.

186
00:09:33.197 --> 00:09:36.033
In fact. I was thinking
Lotte World Olympics.

187
00:09:36.117 --> 00:09:38.160
you and me. a night-long showdown.

188
00:09:38.244 --> 00:09:42.164
- That is. if you can handle it.
- I never back down from a challenge.

189
00:09:42.248 --> 00:09:44.250
[energetic music playing]

190
00:09:45.960 --> 00:09:47.044
[snaps photo]

191
00:09:47.962 --> 00:09:50.923
- It's so cute.
- [crowd clamoring]

192
00:09:56.095 --> 00:09:58.139
I'm sorry Praveena couldn't be here.

193
00:09:58.222 --> 00:10:02.018
Yeah. I mean. she's off
on a college tour in Switzerland.

194
00:10:02.101 --> 00:10:05.396
You know that poli-sci program's
gonna be an amazing fit for her?

195
00:10:05.479 --> 00:10:07.189
She's gonna run the world someday.

196
00:10:07.273 --> 00:10:08.691
[scoffs] Uh…

197
00:10:08.774 --> 00:10:11.819
She didn't say anything about that to me.

198
00:10:11.902 --> 00:10:15.865
I only know about it because
she texted me for dinner recs.

199
00:10:17.158 --> 00:10:18.159
Is that weird?

200
00:10:19.327 --> 00:10:21.871
I think it's cool
that you guys are friends.

201
00:10:22.788 --> 00:10:23.789
[softly] Okay.

202
00:10:24.749 --> 00:10:26.792
Oh. there's the Gyro Drop. Guys. let's go.

203
00:10:26.876 --> 00:10:30.087
Are you kidding me? That line is insane.

204
00:10:31.422 --> 00:10:32.632
That's how rides work.

205
00:10:32.715 --> 00:10:33.966
Ugh. To be honest.

206
00:10:34.050 --> 00:10:36.594
I've only ever done this
with a personal concierge.

207
00:10:36.677 --> 00:10:39.347
[Juliana] Yeah. Yuri and I used
to come here to escape our parents.

208
00:10:39.430 --> 00:10:43.559
I mean. no lines.
gourmet food. VIP everything.

209
00:10:43.643 --> 00:10:45.978
- [groans]
- It was pretty nice. wasn't it?

210
00:10:46.062 --> 00:10:47.063
It was.

211
00:10:47.146 --> 00:10:50.316
- Now I can barely afford to do my nails.
- [chuckles]

212
00:10:50.399 --> 00:10:54.362
Ugh. I miss being rich!
I hate waiting in line.

213
00:10:54.445 --> 00:10:55.571
How about this?

214
00:10:55.655 --> 00:10:58.199
I'll be your personal concierge.
free of charge.

215
00:10:58.282 --> 00:11:00.076
and you're still gonna have fun.

216
00:11:02.244 --> 00:11:03.329
[chuckles]

217
00:11:04.413 --> 00:11:05.998
- Okay.
- [laughs]

218
00:11:11.170 --> 00:11:15.091
You see? All those people rode the ride
and lived to tell the tale.

219
00:11:16.676 --> 00:11:18.761
[in Korean] You said it wasn't scary!

220
00:11:20.513 --> 00:11:23.265
- [in English] Oh my God.
- [retching. coughs]

221
00:11:23.766 --> 00:11:26.560
Okay. maybe not elegantly.

222
00:11:26.644 --> 00:11:30.231
Did you not see what I saw?
It's too steep. Your seatbelt could snap.

223
00:11:30.314 --> 00:11:32.024
You could fly out during that bigass loop.

224
00:11:32.108 --> 00:11:34.735
Then you're in the dark.
and you have no idea what's next.

225
00:11:34.819 --> 00:11:37.196
- Yes. that's the fun of it.
- [sighs]

226
00:11:37.279 --> 00:11:40.574
I'm sorry. you were
so excited about this yesterday.

227
00:11:40.658 --> 00:11:41.951
What changed?

228
00:11:42.034 --> 00:11:43.452
I don't know exactly.

229
00:11:45.329 --> 00:11:47.915
You say you want
to work your way up. right?

230
00:11:48.499 --> 00:11:50.584
Then let's work our way up.

231
00:11:52.044 --> 00:11:54.463
First. we start off
with the Dream Boats. Entry level.

232
00:11:54.547 --> 00:11:56.090
- It barely counts.
- I don't wanna--

233
00:11:56.173 --> 00:12:00.344
Then the bumper cars. Adventurous.
but at least you're in control.

234
00:12:00.428 --> 00:12:01.804
Then the Tomb of Horror.

235
00:12:01.887 --> 00:12:03.681
The rush of adrenaline.

236
00:12:04.223 --> 00:12:05.307
And finally…

237
00:12:06.016 --> 00:12:07.727
the French Revolution.

238
00:12:08.811 --> 00:12:10.104
How's that sound?

239
00:12:11.063 --> 00:12:14.150
- Fine.
- Yay! Come on.

240
00:12:14.233 --> 00:12:17.278
["Go Big or Go Home" playing]

241
00:12:20.823 --> 00:12:22.491
That wasn't so bad. right?

242
00:12:29.790 --> 00:12:32.460
<i>♪ Let's go. go. go ♪</i>

243
00:12:32.543 --> 00:12:35.045
[song continues in Korean]

244
00:12:39.425 --> 00:12:41.093
- Whoo!
- [both laugh]

245
00:12:43.000 --> 00:12:49.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

246
00:12:57.943 --> 00:13:01.447
<i>♪ We going. going. going ♪</i>

247
00:13:01.530 --> 00:13:03.783
<i>♪ We ride ♪</i>

248
00:13:03.866 --> 00:13:07.536
<i>♪ I'm feeling. feeling</i>
<i>Feeling all right ♪</i>

249
00:13:07.620 --> 00:13:11.123
<i>♪ We going. going. going we ride ♪</i>

250
00:13:11.207 --> 00:13:12.666
<i>♪ We ride ♪</i>

251
00:13:12.750 --> 00:13:14.752
<i>♪ Go big or go home ♪</i>

252
00:13:20.341 --> 00:13:22.343
[song continues in Korean]

253
00:13:27.473 --> 00:13:29.683
[all scream]

254
00:13:32.311 --> 00:13:34.355
- Whoo!
- [both laugh]

255
00:13:40.486 --> 00:13:41.904
[thunder rumbles]

256
00:13:41.987 --> 00:13:43.948
Oh no. No. I hate this.

257
00:13:44.031 --> 00:13:45.574
I hate this very much.

258
00:13:45.658 --> 00:13:49.370
If you can survive the Tomb of Horror.
a rollercoaster's nothing.

259
00:13:49.453 --> 00:13:51.664
- [screams]
- [both yelp]

260
00:13:52.164 --> 00:13:55.251
- Okay. but that came out of nowhere.
- Mm-hmm.

261
00:13:55.334 --> 00:13:56.877
Listen. this is the last step.

262
00:13:56.961 --> 00:13:58.754
- [air sprays]
- [both scream]

263
00:13:59.463 --> 00:14:02.341
[Min Ho] Tackling the fear of the unknown.

264
00:14:02.424 --> 00:14:05.803
And is some random in makeup
really that scary?

265
00:14:05.886 --> 00:14:07.137
Uh…

266
00:14:07.221 --> 00:14:09.223
- [shouts]
- [both scream]

267
00:14:09.306 --> 00:14:11.851
- [shrieks]
- [actor gasps]

268
00:14:11.934 --> 00:14:14.353
- [chuckles]
- What?

269
00:14:14.854 --> 00:14:17.648
All right. Covey.
I knew you had it in you.

270
00:14:19.942 --> 00:14:21.986
You let me win a couple.
I suck at basketball.

271
00:14:22.069 --> 00:14:25.614
What? No. No.
No. you're… you're really great.

272
00:14:25.698 --> 00:14:27.199
Uh-huh. That's what I thought.

273
00:14:27.283 --> 00:14:29.952
Ah. I don't know.
I know how much you miss competing.

274
00:14:30.035 --> 00:14:33.956
And I thought it'd be fun for us
to get back into it like the old days.

275
00:14:34.039 --> 00:14:38.252
- Don't you miss being on the track team?
- So that's what this was all about?

276
00:14:38.335 --> 00:14:41.797
Maybe it did sting when you beat
my record. but it's not that I miss track.

277
00:14:41.881 --> 00:14:45.759
It's just… Since I've left.
I've been feeling kind of lost.

278
00:14:45.843 --> 00:14:47.136
Like I don't have a thing.

279
00:14:47.219 --> 00:14:50.055
I'd be more than happy
to help you find whatever that thing is.

280
00:14:50.139 --> 00:14:51.223
because I love you.

281
00:14:51.307 --> 00:14:54.143
[tender music playing]

282
00:14:55.686 --> 00:14:56.896
I love you too.

283
00:15:20.794 --> 00:15:24.465
Well. I did say it first.
so I guess that means I win.

284
00:15:24.548 --> 00:15:26.342
- Okay. let's go.
- [chuckles]

285
00:15:26.425 --> 00:15:28.427
[excited chatter]

286
00:15:30.095 --> 00:15:32.097
Breathe. Covey. You got this.

287
00:15:32.765 --> 00:15:35.768
Holy crap!
Eunice and Min Ho are on Discatch.

288
00:15:36.810 --> 00:15:39.480
- Oh my God!
- [scoffs]

289
00:15:39.563 --> 00:15:41.273
"After a whirlwind summer tour.

290
00:15:41.357 --> 00:15:43.609
Eunice and her manager
were spotted at Lotte World."

291
00:15:43.692 --> 00:15:46.403
[Eunice] "Her manager
is Young Moon's son. Min Ho.

292
00:15:46.487 --> 00:15:49.740
a promising producer
who has a bright future of his own."

293
00:15:49.823 --> 00:15:52.076
Hell yeah. your future's bright.

294
00:15:52.576 --> 00:15:55.537
Damn. I didn't realize
they followed you everywhere.

295
00:15:55.621 --> 00:15:57.206
Rome. Paris. Dubai.

296
00:15:57.289 --> 00:15:59.875
Min Ho? Babes.
are you taking acting clients?

297
00:15:59.959 --> 00:16:03.629
Zendaya's making her directorial debut.
and if I could just get one audition…

298
00:16:03.712 --> 00:16:05.631
Guys. Guys. grades are in. [gasps]

299
00:16:05.714 --> 00:16:07.007
Oh my gosh!

300
00:16:07.091 --> 00:16:09.009
[Juliana] Okay. vibe shift.

301
00:16:09.093 --> 00:16:11.679
Yes! I aced everything.

302
00:16:11.762 --> 00:16:13.681
I still have a shot at SNU.

303
00:16:13.764 --> 00:16:16.016
Got an A in Anatomy. obvi.

304
00:16:16.100 --> 00:16:19.144
Ooh! Me too. Take that. Professor Choi.

305
00:16:19.728 --> 00:16:21.689
[Kitty] <i>Rip the Band-Aid off. Kitty.</i>

306
00:16:21.772 --> 00:16:24.149
[gentle music playing]

307
00:16:24.233 --> 00:16:25.275
<i>Wait.</i>

308
00:16:25.901 --> 00:16:27.361
<i>I need more time.</i>

309
00:16:28.404 --> 00:16:32.658
<i>Any version of the future I want</i>
<i>is on the other side of these grades.</i>

310
00:16:33.158 --> 00:16:36.120
<i>NYU. which I've been dreaming about</i>
<i>since the summer.</i>

311
00:16:36.203 --> 00:16:40.708
<i>and the fantasy of Seoul with Min Ho</i>
<i>that's been in my head all day.</i>

312
00:16:41.875 --> 00:16:43.961
[sighs] <i>I just need more time.</i>

313
00:16:44.044 --> 00:16:46.046
[roller coaster rattles on tracks]

314
00:16:48.590 --> 00:16:51.802
- Well. how did you do?
- I can't do this.

315
00:16:51.885 --> 00:16:54.847
- I'm not ready for something this huge.
- Wait. you're leaving?

316
00:16:54.930 --> 00:16:56.098
But our photo.

317
00:16:56.181 --> 00:16:57.933
I'm sorry. I… I can't.

318
00:16:58.017 --> 00:16:59.852
Well. if you're not going. I'm not going.

319
00:16:59.935 --> 00:17:02.229
No. I'll feel worse
if you don't do it because of me.

320
00:17:02.312 --> 00:17:04.023
- So…
- Covey. wait.

321
00:17:04.106 --> 00:17:05.607
[gentle music playing]

322
00:17:05.691 --> 00:17:07.860
This isn't about the ride. is it?

323
00:17:08.777 --> 00:17:10.654
You guys have fun.
I wanna hear all about it.

324
00:17:10.738 --> 00:17:12.948
See you at the exit. Sorry. Excuse me.

325
00:17:13.407 --> 00:17:14.241
[in Korean] Sorry.

326
00:17:14.324 --> 00:17:15.659
[in English] Sorry.

327
00:17:15.743 --> 00:17:16.952
Excuse me.

328
00:17:23.917 --> 00:17:26.170
What are you doing here? [sighs]

329
00:17:26.253 --> 00:17:29.923
I already told you. I don't do
death traps from the '80s. Kathy.

330
00:17:30.007 --> 00:17:33.427
Oh. So all that decapitation talk was
'cause you were scared?

331
00:17:33.510 --> 00:17:35.054
Not 'cause you were trying to get to me?

332
00:17:35.137 --> 00:17:37.514
Look. I know you think
I'm some big. bad Disney villain.

333
00:17:37.598 --> 00:17:38.849
but even I have limits.

334
00:17:38.932 --> 00:17:40.225
What am I supposed to think?

335
00:17:40.309 --> 00:17:42.936
You've been messing with my relationship
ever since you got here.

336
00:17:43.020 --> 00:17:45.689
Because you've been
messing with my friendship with Q.

337
00:17:45.773 --> 00:17:48.859
Friendship? Come on. I'm not blind.

338
00:17:48.942 --> 00:17:51.528
He's my best friend.
of course I'm gonna protect him.

339
00:17:51.612 --> 00:17:56.033
Look. there is a lot
that you don't understand about us. okay?

340
00:17:56.116 --> 00:17:58.994
When we were together.
I was dating someone else too.

341
00:17:59.078 --> 00:18:00.079
A girl.

342
00:18:00.162 --> 00:18:02.748
And I was trying to figure out
what I was into.

343
00:18:02.831 --> 00:18:05.876
and it… it really got messy. and…

344
00:18:06.877 --> 00:18:08.587
You… you wouldn't get it.

345
00:18:12.424 --> 00:18:13.634
Actually. I do.

346
00:18:13.717 --> 00:18:18.514
I broke up with Dae for Yuri.
and then I kissed Yuri

347
00:18:18.597 --> 00:18:22.351
when she was dating Juliana.
and I was kind of seeing Praveena.

348
00:18:23.060 --> 00:18:25.104
None of those were my brightest moments.

349
00:18:25.187 --> 00:18:30.275
But looking back now. I can see all those
missteps led me to discovering who I am.

350
00:18:31.443 --> 00:18:34.530
Well. mine got me further
from who I want to be with.

351
00:18:35.239 --> 00:18:38.992
And I'm pretty sure
that door's closing now. so…

352
00:18:39.701 --> 00:18:41.912
Yeah. I think it is.

353
00:18:43.413 --> 00:18:45.415
[riders scream]

354
00:18:49.128 --> 00:18:53.715
If I'm being honest. that is
what I've been freaking out about all day.

355
00:18:54.466 --> 00:18:58.804
The fact that a door could be closing
for me here in Seoul.

356
00:18:59.471 --> 00:19:00.472
What do you mean?

357
00:19:01.265 --> 00:19:03.600
If I blow it on these midterms.

358
00:19:04.101 --> 00:19:09.857
the possibility of me
having a future in Seoul is gone.

359
00:19:10.357 --> 00:19:14.361
and the life that I love
with all of my friends.

360
00:19:14.444 --> 00:19:16.864
And… Min Ho.

361
00:19:23.579 --> 00:19:26.081
But I think the biggest mistake

362
00:19:26.582 --> 00:19:29.918
would be to let my grades decide
if I get the life that I want.

363
00:19:30.752 --> 00:19:32.087
I get to decide that.

364
00:19:40.429 --> 00:19:42.472
[gasps] Holy shit. I killed it!

365
00:19:43.473 --> 00:19:45.058
I have to go tell Min Ho.

366
00:19:50.314 --> 00:19:51.481
Marius?

367
00:19:52.649 --> 00:19:56.069
For what it's worth.
I think I was too quick to judge you.

368
00:19:56.153 --> 00:19:58.488
[chuckles softly] Thanks. Kitty.

369
00:19:59.531 --> 00:20:02.367
- Did you just say my name?
- Don't make it a thing.

370
00:20:02.451 --> 00:20:03.911
Oh. it's a thing.

371
00:20:04.661 --> 00:20:06.538
[upbeat music playing]

372
00:20:06.622 --> 00:20:10.292
Sorry. I'm just coming through.
Thank you. Thank you. Sorry. Sorry. Sorry.

373
00:20:10.375 --> 00:20:12.294
Thank you. Just going this way. Thank you.

374
00:20:12.377 --> 00:20:13.837
[in Korean] I'm sorry.

375
00:20:13.921 --> 00:20:16.423
[in English] I'm so sorry.
Excuse me. Min Ho!

376
00:20:17.424 --> 00:20:18.800
I did well on my midterms.

377
00:20:18.884 --> 00:20:20.052
I told you!

378
00:20:22.429 --> 00:20:23.972
You're relieved now?

379
00:20:24.056 --> 00:20:25.557
Yes. It means…

380
00:20:25.641 --> 00:20:30.646
It's possible that you could be here
next year and we could…

381
00:20:32.231 --> 00:20:37.277
Yeah. it's possible.
I'm ready for whatever happens next.

382
00:20:40.906 --> 00:20:42.366
You ready to take this ride with me?

383
00:20:43.158 --> 00:20:48.705
[chanting] Kitty! Kitty!
Kitty! Kitty! Kitty! Kitty!

384
00:20:48.789 --> 00:20:50.290
Why do you think I came back?

385
00:20:50.374 --> 00:20:51.667
- Yes!
- [cheering]

386
00:20:51.750 --> 00:20:53.210
["Soñar" playing]

387
00:20:53.293 --> 00:20:54.461
<i>♪ Drop it ♪</i>

388
00:20:54.544 --> 00:20:56.672
[song continues in Korean]

389
00:21:04.304 --> 00:21:05.847
[screaming]

390
00:21:08.934 --> 00:21:12.312
- [high-energy pop fades]
- [gentle music playing]

391
00:21:15.899 --> 00:21:17.609
- Uh… [groans]
- [gasps]

392
00:21:17.693 --> 00:21:19.278
[retching]

393
00:21:19.361 --> 00:21:21.863
Yep. Those loop-de-loops will get you.

394
00:21:21.947 --> 00:21:23.949
[crowd clamoring]

395
00:21:26.368 --> 00:21:28.745
Don't take my picture!
I said stop!

396
00:21:29.329 --> 00:21:32.457
You were right. Lotte World is really fun.

397
00:21:32.541 --> 00:21:35.335
- Even these silly uniforms.
- [chuckles]

398
00:21:35.419 --> 00:21:37.337
Sorry I was such a grump.

399
00:21:37.421 --> 00:21:39.756
Wow. really? I couldn't tell.

400
00:21:39.840 --> 00:21:42.134
Ms. Ahn? Eunice needs help.

401
00:21:42.217 --> 00:21:44.761
I'm coming. Back to being the grown-ups.

402
00:21:45.804 --> 00:21:49.141
- [clamoring]
- Everyone! Hey. hey. hey! Everyone!

403
00:21:51.184 --> 00:21:52.686
Okay. don't laugh.

404
00:21:52.769 --> 00:21:55.731
But I've been thinking about joining
the Future Business Leaders Club.

405
00:21:55.814 --> 00:21:58.233
Are you kidding?
You'd look great in a three-piece suit.

406
00:21:58.317 --> 00:22:01.361
Aww. Oh. I left my bag at the gift shop.
But I'll be right back.

407
00:22:01.445 --> 00:22:03.071
Oh. yeah. I'll save you a seat.

408
00:22:12.414 --> 00:22:15.625
Okay. today's been really great.
so you can save the snark.

409
00:22:16.918 --> 00:22:21.048
[quietly] Okay. Okay.
How about the truth. then?

410
00:22:22.174 --> 00:22:23.592
Look. I know you're with Jin.

411
00:22:23.675 --> 00:22:26.219
and I know I've been messing with that
since I came back.

412
00:22:26.928 --> 00:22:31.850
But the truth is. I'm having a hard time
accepting we might be a thing of the past.

413
00:22:31.933 --> 00:22:34.561
Because you're the reason I came back.

414
00:22:35.145 --> 00:22:39.691
Q. you're the only reason I am here.
because I want to be with you.

415
00:22:39.775 --> 00:22:41.777
[somber music playing]

416
00:22:47.699 --> 00:22:49.826
[in Korean] Checking your grades again?

417
00:22:49.910 --> 00:22:53.872
Why were you so worried?
You've never gotten less than an A.

418
00:22:53.955 --> 00:22:55.832
If I get even one bad grade.

419
00:22:55.916 --> 00:22:58.043
there’s a chance that I won’t get
into Seoul National University.

420
00:22:58.126 --> 00:23:00.629
I know that's the path
you have always talked about.

421
00:23:00.712 --> 00:23:02.589
but you have more options now.

422
00:23:03.131 --> 00:23:07.469
I used to think I'd always be a VIP.

423
00:23:07.552 --> 00:23:10.639
Honestly. today while we were out.

424
00:23:11.264 --> 00:23:13.558
you showed me
there's more than one way to live.

425
00:23:14.851 --> 00:23:17.229
Both of our lives are different now.

426
00:23:17.979 --> 00:23:21.316
[in English] So give yourself
permission to dream.

427
00:23:21.400 --> 00:23:22.401
Okay?

428
00:23:24.194 --> 00:23:26.571
[clicks tongue] I still can't believe
you paid for this.

429
00:23:26.655 --> 00:23:28.698
You could've just took
a picture of the monitor.

430
00:23:28.782 --> 00:23:31.410
- Okay. some things are worth the splurge.
- [sighs]

431
00:23:31.493 --> 00:23:32.494
Kitty. look.

432
00:23:33.370 --> 00:23:36.289
Ah! It's perfect.

433
00:23:36.790 --> 00:23:40.293
How did our moms manage to look cute?
I look like I've been electrocuted.

434
00:23:40.377 --> 00:23:42.379
Hey. you look happy.

435
00:23:42.462 --> 00:23:45.048
- And electrocuted. [chuckles]
- Mm.

436
00:23:48.385 --> 00:23:51.763
[Kitty] <i>I love that I'm walking</i>
<i>in my mom's footsteps in Seoul.</i>

437
00:23:51.847 --> 00:23:55.308
<i>But now I believe that</i>
<i>I can forge my own path here too.</i>

438
00:23:56.268 --> 00:23:58.353
- Ready for <i>bingsu?</i>
<i>- </i>Yes.

439
00:23:58.854 --> 00:24:02.441
You think that Eunice might want to come?
She could probably use a pick-me-up.

440
00:24:02.524 --> 00:24:04.985
Uh. she said she was gonna crash.
Today was a lot.

441
00:24:05.068 --> 00:24:07.737
That's fair. I guess
both your lives are about to change.

442
00:24:07.821 --> 00:24:09.197
Wait. let me get my jacket.

443
00:24:09.281 --> 00:24:10.657
[cell phone chimes]

444
00:24:20.459 --> 00:24:22.419
{\an8}[Kitty] Okay. I am ready to go.

445
00:24:22.502 --> 00:24:28.383
Actually. um. I hate to do this.
but Marius says he needs to talk.

446
00:24:28.467 --> 00:24:32.846
- I know how you feel about him. but--
- No. Marius is…

447
00:24:32.929 --> 00:24:36.057
I'm gonna give him the benefit of
the doubt. You go. You're a good friend.

448
00:24:36.725 --> 00:24:39.769
- I promise I'll make it up to you.
- I'll allow it.

449
00:24:41.771 --> 00:24:43.023
- Bye.
- Bye.

450
00:24:53.241 --> 00:24:55.535
[Kitty] <i>Today was</i>
<i>an emotional rollercoaster.</i>

451
00:24:55.619 --> 00:24:57.162
<i>to say the least.</i>

452
00:24:57.245 --> 00:25:01.041
<i>But my life wouldn't be mine</i>
<i>if it didn't have its ups and downs.</i>

453
00:25:02.000 --> 00:25:04.878
<i>Once upon a time. KISS was just a dream.</i>

454
00:25:05.670 --> 00:25:07.297
<i>But now. it's home.</i>

455
00:25:08.381 --> 00:25:10.717
<i>My friends are my family.</i>

456
00:25:11.676 --> 00:25:13.512
<i>And Min Ho…</i>

457
00:25:14.054 --> 00:25:18.225
<i>Well. there's no one else</i>
<i>I'd rather take this ride with.</i>

458
00:25:21.645 --> 00:25:22.812
[in Korean] So. what's wrong?

459
00:25:25.398 --> 00:25:28.735
[Kitty in English] <i>There's no one</i>
<i>I trust more to catch me when I fall.</i>

460
00:25:29.361 --> 00:25:31.905
<i>There's no one like…</i>

461
00:25:31.988 --> 00:25:33.073
<i>Min Ho?</i>

462
00:25:34.074 --> 00:25:35.075
<i>And…</i>

463
00:25:35.158 --> 00:25:36.785
<i>Eunice?</i>

464
00:25:38.495 --> 00:25:39.913
[in Korean] Min Ho…

465
00:25:39.996 --> 00:25:41.414
[splutters]

466
00:25:42.832 --> 00:25:44.000
I…

467
00:25:44.084 --> 00:25:45.710
[sighs. sniffles]

468
00:25:47.045 --> 00:25:48.713
I think I'm pregnant.

469
00:25:49.881 --> 00:25:50.966
[scoffs]

470
00:25:51.049 --> 00:25:53.051
[somber music playing]

471
00:25:55.512 --> 00:25:56.513
Paris…

472
